  "projectDescription": "This is a python project in PyCharm.\r\nAdd an additional window for configuration and logger. Claude md needs contain instructions for using sonnenbatterie, homewizard, NRO data etc ",
  "workplanContent": "# Workplan\n\n\u003C!-- Generated by ClaudeContextGenerator \u2014 review and adjust before creating YouTrack tickets --\u003E\n\n**Total estimated time:** 12.5d\n\n## 1. Setup Project Structure and Development Environment\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 0.5d\n\nCreate the project directory structure following the specified architecture with proper separation of concerns. Set up pyproject.toml with all dependencies, configure development tools (black, ruff, mypy), and establish pre-commit hooks. Initialize git repository and create basic CI/CD configuration files.\n\n## 2. Implement Core Configuration Data Models\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1d\n\nDevelop Pydantic v2 models for all configuration entities including DeviceConfig, SonnenBatterieConfig, HomeWizardConfig, and SolarEdgeConfig. Implement comprehensive validation rules with custom validators for IP addresses, ports, and device-specific parameters. Create configuration loading and validation utilities with proper error handling.\n\n## 3. Create Database Schema and Repository Pattern\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1d\n\nDesign and implement SQLAlchemy 2.0 models for device readings, system state, and configuration history. Create Alembic migrations for initial schema. Implement repository pattern with async SQLAlchemy, including base repository class and specific repositories for each entity. Add unit of work pattern for transaction management.\n\n## 4. Build Abstract Device Client Interface\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 4h\n\nCreate the abstract DeviceClient base class with standardized methods for device communication. Define DeviceReading dataclass and common error types. Implement factory pattern for device client instantiation and registry system for different device types.\n\n## 5. Implement sonnenBatterie Integration Client\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1d\n\nDevelop the sonnenBatterie client with support for both v1 and v2 APIs. Implement automatic API version detection, secure token management, and connection pooling. Add comprehensive error handling with circuit breaker pattern and retry logic. Include data validation and normalization for USOC and power readings.\n\n## 6. Implement HomeWizard Device Integration\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1d\n\nCreate HomeWizard device client with auto-discovery via mDNS/SSDP scanning. Implement device-specific logic for different HomeWizard devices (P1 meter, car charger, solar meter). Add calibration procedures and multi-device support with redundancy handling. Include real-time validation and threshold management.\n\n## 7. Implement SolarEdge Modbus Control Client\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1.5d\n\nDevelop SolarEdge Modbus client with safety-first design including pre-flight checks and command verification. Implement gradual power ramping, status monitoring, and fault detection. Add comprehensive safety mechanisms including emergency stops and rate limiting. Create read-back confirmation system for all control commands.\n\n## 8. Create ENTSO-E Price Data Integration\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1d\n\nImplement multi-source price data strategy with ENTSO-E Transparency Platform as primary source. Add secondary APIs and fallback mechanisms using local database with historical patterns. Create price data validation, interpolation for gaps, and short-term forecasting. Include CSV import functionality for testing scenarios.\n\n## 9. Build Decision Engine and Rule System\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1.5d\n\nImplement strategy pattern-based decision engine with pluggable rules for battery management and pricing strategies. Create rule validation system with dry-run capabilities. Add SoC threshold management with hysteresis, charging/discharging rate limits, and safety override controls. Include comprehensive decision logging and audit trails.\n\n## 10. Develop FastAPI Web Interface and REST APIs\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1d\n\nCreate FastAPI application with RESTful endpoints for device status, configuration management, and system control. Implement dependency injection for service layers and add comprehensive API documentation with OpenAPI. Create health check endpoints and real-time WebSocket connections for live data streaming.\n\n## 11. Create Configuration GUI Application\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 2d\n\nBuild modern tabbed configuration interface using tkinter with ttk styling. Implement all four configuration tabs (Device Configuration, Decision Logic, System \u0026 Monitoring, Validation \u0026 Deployment) with real-time validation and testing capabilities. Add configuration import/export, versioning, and backup functionality with encryption support.\n\n## 12. Implement Structured Logging and Monitoring System\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1d\n\nSet up structlog with comprehensive logging categories and levels. Create real-time log viewer with filtering, search, and export capabilities. Implement metrics collection for KPIs including response times, success rates, and system resources. Add dashboard integration with alerting and automated reporting.\n\n## 13. Write Comprehensive Test Suite\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 1.5d\n\nDevelop unit tests achieving \u003E90% code coverage using pytest and pytest-asyncio. Create integration tests for device communication and end-to-end workflows. Implement property-based testing with hypothesis for edge cases. Add performance tests for high-frequency operations and contract tests for API compatibility. Create test fixtures and mocks for all external dependencies.\n\n## 14. Create Documentation and Deployment Guides\n\n- [ ] **Estimated time:** 0.5d\n\nWrite comprehensive documentation using MkDocs with Material theme. Create installation guides, configuration tutorials, and operational procedures. Document all APIs with examples and create troubleshooting guides. Add deployment procedures with rollback capabilities and maintenance automation scripts."
